title: Phillipsburg boys soccer tops Newton, advances to H/W/S final (PHOTOS)
text:
Complete Box Score Â» 
Alec Coleman put the Stateliners ahead and then provided some insurance as Phillipsburg High School's boys soccer team booked another trip to the Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex Tournament final. 
Coleman scored twice -- on a first-half penalty kick and a second-half header -- as Phillipsburg defeated host Newton 3-1 in the county semifinals on Saturday. 
The third-seeded Stateliners advance to play top-seeded Warren Hills, which defeated High Point, in the championship game on Halloween. 
Devin Dowd opened the scoring for Phillipsburg, which lost to North Hunterdon in the county final last season. 
Alejandro Patino had Newton's only score on a penalty kick. 
Click through the gallery atop this post to see photos from Saturday's game.
